{
  "text": "The reaction of pharmacological active ionic liquid H + N(CH 2 CH 2 OH) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , which have a structure of metallated ionic liquid. It is the first example of the conversion of a protic ionic liquid into metallated ionic liquid (compound 1 \u2192 3 \u2192 5). The structure of 5 has been proved by X-ray diffraction analysis. The investigation of physiological activity of metallated ionic liquids will be conducted in a new future. ",
